<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8"/>
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
<title>Bombsite — Dimitra Dimitriou</title>

<link href="https://api.fontshare.com/v2/css?f[]=switzer@400,300,500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<link href="https://api.fontshare.com/v2/css?f[]=ciclo@400,700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/gsap/3.12.5/gsap.min.js"></script>
<script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/gsap/3.12.5/ScrollTrigger.min.js"></script>

<style>
*,*::before,*::after{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box;}
:root{
  --beige:#e8e0d0;
  --beige-dim:#c4b99a;
  --bg:#0b0810;
  --bomb:#ff006e;
  --bomb-dim:#c77dff;
  --bomb-dark:#0d0612;
  --font-display:'Ciclo',Georgia,serif;
  --font-body:'Switzer',system-ui,sans-serif;
}
html{scroll-behavior:smooth;}
body{
  background:var(--bg);
  color:var(--beige);
  font-family:var(--font-body);
  font-weight:300;
  overflow-x:hidden;
  cursor:none;
}

/* ── CURSOR ── */
#cursor-dot{position:fixed;width:6px;height:6px;background:var(--bomb);border-radius:50%;pointer-events:none;z-index:9999;transform:translate(-50%,-50%);mix-blend-mode:screen;}
#cursor-ring{position:fixed;width:32px;height:32px;border:1px solid rgba(199,125,255,.35);border-radius:50%;pointer-events:none;z-index:9998;transform:translate(-50%,-50%);transition:width .28s,height .28s,border-color .3s;}
#cursor-ring.grow{width:54px;height:54px;border-color:rgba(199,125,255,.65);}

/* ── CHROME ── */
#back-nav{
  position:fixed;top:2.2rem;left:2.8rem;z-index:200;
  font-family:var(--font-body);font-size:11px;font-weight:400;
  letter-spacing:.12em;color:rgba(232,228,220,.28);
  text-decoration:none;text-transform:uppercase;
  transition:color .3s;cursor:none;
}
#back-nav:hover{color:var(--beige-dim);}

#progress-bar{
  position:fixed;top:0;left:0;height:1px;
  background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--bomb-dim),var(--bomb));
  z-index:300;width:0%;transition:width .1s linear;
}

/* ── HERO ── */
#hero{
  position:relative;min-height:100vh;
  display:flex;align-items:flex-end;
  overflow:hidden;
  background:var(--bomb-dark);
}
#hero-canvas{position:absolute;inset:0;width:100%;height:100%;}
.hero-inner{
  position:relative;z-index:10;
  padding:0 9rem 6rem;
  max-width:1200px;
}
.hero-meta{
  font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.26em;text-transform:uppercase;
  color:rgba(199,125,255,.45);margin-bottom:1.4rem;
  display:flex;align-items:center;gap:1.2rem;
}
.hero-meta::before{content:'';width:32px;height:1px;background:rgba(199,125,255,.3);}
.hero-title{
  font-family:var(--font-display);
  font-size:clamp(4rem,9vw,8.5rem);
  font-weight:400;line-height:.95;
  color:var(--beige);
  margin-bottom:2rem;
}
.hero-title .glitch{position:relative;display:inline-block;}
.hero-title .glitch::before,.hero-title .glitch::after{content:attr(data-text);position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;}
.hero-title .glitch::before{color:#ff006e;clip-path:polygon(0 18%,100% 18%,100% 38%,0 38%);animation:ga 5s steps(1) infinite;}
.hero-title .glitch::after{color:#00f5d4;clip-path:polygon(0 58%,100% 58%,100% 78%,0 78%);animation:gb 5s steps(1) infinite;}
@keyframes ga{0%,80%,82%,100%{transform:none;opacity:0;}81%{transform:skewX(-14deg) translateX(-5px);opacity:.55;}}
@keyframes gb{0%,80%,83%,100%{transform:none;opacity:0;}82%{transform:skewX(9deg) translateX(5px);opacity:.55;}}

.hero-desc{
  font-size:1rem;font-weight:300;line-height:1.85;
  color:rgba(232,228,220,.45);max-width:560px;
  margin-bottom:2.8rem;
}
.hero-tags{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:8px;}
.hero-tag{
  font-size:8px;letter-spacing:.2em;text-transform:uppercase;
  padding:5px 13px;border:1px solid rgba(199,125,255,.3);
  color:rgba(199,125,255,.65);
}
.hero-year{
  position:absolute;bottom:6rem;right:9rem;
  font-size:9px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;
  color:rgba(232,228,220,.2);
}

/* ── SECTIONS ── */
.proj-section{
  padding:8rem 9rem;
  position:relative;
  border-top:1px solid rgba(199,125,255,.06);
}

.section-label{
  font-size:9px;letter-spacing:.28em;text-transform:uppercase;
  color:rgba(199,125,255,.35);margin-bottom:3.5rem;
  display:flex;align-items:center;gap:1rem;
}
.section-label::before{content:'';width:24px;height:1px;background:rgba(199,125,255,.25);}

.section-heading{
  font-family:var(--font-display);
  font-size:clamp(1.8rem,3.5vw,3rem);
  font-weight:400;color:var(--beige);
  line-height:1.1;margin-bottom:1.2rem;
}

.section-body{
  font-size:.95rem;font-weight:300;line-height:1.9;
  color:rgba(232,228,220,.5);max-width:520px;
}

/* ── CONTEXT SPLIT ── */
#context-section{
  background:linear-gradient(135deg,#18112a 0%,#120e1e 50%,#0e0d18 100%);
}
#context{
  display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;
  align-items:center;gap:5rem;
}
.context-image{position:relative;}

/* ── CSS iMAC FRAME ── */
.imac-wrap{
  width:100%;
  display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;
  filter:drop-shadow(0 24px 60px rgba(80,40,140,.5));
}
.imac-body{
  width:100%;
  background:linear-gradient(160deg,#2e2a38 0%,#1c1824 60%,#161320 100%);
  border-radius:14px 14px 4px 4px;
  padding:10px 10px 0 10px;
  border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.10);
  box-shadow:
    inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,.12),
    inset 0 -1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,.4),
    0 2px 0 rgba(0,0,0,.6);
  position:relative;
}
.imac-bezel{
  background:#0a0910;
  border-radius:8px 8px 3px 3px;
  padding:18px 14px 12px;
  display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;gap:10px;
  border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.06);
}
.imac-camera{
  width:6px;height:6px;border-radius:50%;
  background:radial-gradient(circle,#3a3a4a,#1a1a22);
  border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.12);
  box-shadow:0 0 0 1px rgba(0,0,0,.5);
}
.imac-screen{
  width:100%;border-radius:3px;
  overflow:hidden;
  border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.08);
  box-shadow:inset 0 0 30px rgba(0,0,0,.3);
  background:#e8ecf0;
  position:relative;
}
.imac-screen::after{
  /* subtle screen glare */
  content:'';position:absolute;inset:0;
  background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(255,255,255,.06) 0%,transparent 50%);
  pointer-events:none;z-index:2;
}
.imac-screen img{
  width:100%;display:block;
  border-radius:2px;
}
.imac-chin{
  height:22px;
  background:linear-gradient(180deg,#1c1824,#201c2c);
  border-radius:0 0 3px 3px;
  border-top:1px solid rgba(0,0,0,.5);
  width:100%;
}
.imac-neck{
  width:18%;height:28px;
  background:linear-gradient(180deg,#252030,#1e1a28);
  clip-path:polygon(20% 0%,80% 0%,90% 100%,10% 100%);
  border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.06);
  border-top:none;
  margin-top:-1px;
}
.imac-base{
  width:38%;height:10px;
  background:linear-gradient(180deg,#2a2535,#1c1826);
  border-radius:0 0 8px 8px;
  border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.07);
  border-top:none;
  box-shadow:0 4px 16px rgba(0,0,0,.5);
}
.context-text{}
.context-text .section-body{margin-bottom:0;}

/* ── SENSORY MAP ── */
#sensory{background:#0e0c18;}
.map-grid{
  display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;
  gap:2.5rem;margin-top:4rem;
}
.map-card{position:relative;}
.map-card img{
  width:100%;display:block;
  border-radius:10px;
  /* no blend mode — maps have light bg, let them sit on a card */
  mix-blend-mode:normal;
  box-shadow:
    0 0 0 1px rgba(199,125,255,.15),
    0 8px 40px rgba(0,0,0,.55),
    0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,.4);
  filter:contrast(1.02) saturate(1.05);
}
.map-caption{
  margin-top:1rem;
  font-size:8.5px;letter-spacing:.14em;text-transform:uppercase;
  color:rgba(232,228,220,.28);line-height:1.6;
}
.map-caption strong{color:rgba(199,125,255,.55);}

.sensory-text-block{
  display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;
  gap:5rem;margin-top:5rem;
  padding-top:4rem;
  border-top:1px solid rgba(199,125,255,.07);
}
.sensory-col .col-title{
  font-family:var(--font-body);font-size:11px;font-weight:500;
  letter-spacing:.16em;text-transform:uppercase;
  color:rgba(199,125,255,.6);margin-bottom:1rem;
}
.sensory-col .col-body{
  font-size:.9rem;font-weight:300;line-height:1.9;
  color:rgba(232,228,220,.45);
}

/* ── INTENT / GALLERY ── */
#intent{}
.gallery-pair{
  display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;
  gap:2rem;margin-top:4rem;
}
.gallery-pair img{
  width:100%;display:block;border-radius:4px;
  border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.06);
}
.intent-text{
  max-width:560px;margin-top:3.5rem;
  font-size:.95rem;font-weight:300;line-height:1.9;
  color:rgba(232,228,220,.45);
}

/* ── MOTION ── */
#motion{background:rgba(0,0,0,.3);}
.motion-layout{
  display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;
  gap:6rem;align-items:start;margin-top:4rem;
}
.motion-left{}
.motion-macbook{
  width:100%;display:block;
  mix-blend-mode:lighten;
}
.motion-link{
  display:inline-block;margin-top:1.5rem;
  font-size:9px;letter-spacing:.2em;text-transform:uppercase;
  color:rgba(199,125,255,.5);text-decoration:none;
  border-bottom:1px solid rgba(199,125,255,.2);padding-bottom:2px;
  transition:color .3s,border-color .3s;cursor:none;
}
.motion-link:hover{color:var(--bomb);border-color:var(--bomb);}
.motion-right{}
.motion-desc{
  font-size:.95rem;font-weight:300;line-height:1.9;
  color:rgba(232,228,220,.45);margin-bottom:3rem;
}
.stills-grid{
  display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;
  gap:1rem;
}
.stills-grid img{
  width:100%;display:block;border-radius:3px;
  border:1px solid rgba(199,125,255,.1);
}

/* ── ZINE ── */
#zine{}
.zine-wrap{
  margin-top:4rem;position:relative;
}
.zine-img{
  width:100%;display:block;border-radius:6px;
}
.zine-caption{
  margin-top:2rem;max-width:520px;
  font-size:.9rem;font-weight:300;line-height:1.9;
  color:rgba(232,228,220,.38);
}

/* ── FOOTER NAV ── */
#footer-nav{
  padding:5rem 9rem 6rem;
  border-top:1px solid rgba(199,125,255,.08);
  display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;
}
.fnav-back{
  font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;
  color:rgba(232,228,220,.25);text-decoration:none;
  transition:color .3s;cursor:none;
}
.fnav-back:hover{color:var(--beige);}
.fnav-sig{
  font-family:var(--font-display);
  font-size:1.1rem;color:rgba(199,125,255,.2);
}

/* ── REVEAL ANIM ── */
.reveal{opacity:0;transform:translateY(32px);}

/* grain overlay */
body::after{
  content:'';position:fixed;inset:0;pointer-events:none;z-index:500;opacity:.025;
  background-image:url("data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg viewBox='0 0 256 256' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cfilter id='n'%3E%3CfeTurbulence type='fractalNoise' baseFrequency='0.9' numOctaves='4' stitchTiles='stitch'/%3E%3C/filter%3E%3Crect width='100%25' height='100%25' filter='url(%23n)'/%3E%3C/svg%3E");
  background-size:180px;
}

/* responsive */
@media(max-width:900px){
  .proj-section{padding:5rem 2.5rem;}
  #context,#intent .gallery-pair,.map-grid,.sensory-text-block,
  .motion-layout,.stills-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr;}
  .hero-inner{padding:0 2.5rem 5rem;}
  .hero-year{right:2.5rem;}
  #footer-nav{padding:4rem 2.5rem 5rem;}
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div id="cursor-dot"></div>
<div id="cursor-ring"></div>
<div id="progress-bar"></div>
<a href="work.html" id="back-nav">← All Work</a>

<!-- ══ HERO ══ -->
<section id="hero">
  <canvas id="hero-canvas"></canvas>
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <p class="hero-meta">03 — Print Media &amp; Motion Graphics</p>
    <h1 class="hero-title">
      <span class="glitch" data-text="Bombsite">Bombsite</span>
    </h1>
    <p class="hero-desc">An exploration of a World War II bombing in Hackney, London — translating historical context into a sensory system through motion, sound, and typography. A dual-mapping system of olfactory incidents and conversational geometries captures the invisible, lived character of a site where past and present collapse into one another.</p>
    <div class="hero-tags">
      <span class="hero-tag">Print Media</span>
      <span class="hero-tag">Motion Graphics</span>
      <span class="hero-tag">Sensory Mapping</span>
      <span class="hero-tag">Typography</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <p class="hero-year">2023 — 2024</p>
</section>

<!-- ══ CONTEXT ══ -->
<section class="proj-section" id="context-section">
  <div id="context">
    <div class="context-image reveal">
      <div class="imac-wrap">
        <div class="imac-body">
          <div class="imac-bezel">
            <div class="imac-camera"></div>
            <div class="imac-screen">
              <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Sensory cartography map of Hackney">
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="imac-chin"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="imac-neck"></div>
        <div class="imac-base"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="context-text">
      <p class="section-label">Context</p>
      <h2 class="section-heading reveal">Memory,<br>mapped.</h2>
      <p class="section-body reveal">This project explores the impact of a World War II bombing in Hackney, London, translating historical context into a sensory system through motion, sound, and typography. The aim is to create an immersive experience that communicates the emotional distortion of memory and connects past and present.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ══ SENSORY CARTOGRAPHY ══ -->
<section class="proj-section" id="sensory">
  <p class="section-label reveal">Methodology</p>
  <h2 class="section-heading reveal">Sensory Cartography<br>&amp; Social Flux</h2>
  <p class="section-body reveal">To capture the invisible character of the site, a dual-mapping system was developed: Point Data (dots) to isolate specific olfactory triggers, and Polygonal Zones to define the reach and density of ambient conversations. This methodology allowed visualisation of how ephemeral sensory layers overlap to create the unique 'social friction' of the location.</p>

  <div class="map-grid">
    <div class="map-card reveal">
      <img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="Olfactory incidents map — dot layer">
      <p class="map-caption"><strong>Olfactory Incidents (The Dots)</strong> — Point-based mapping of specific scent sources, recording their frequency and location to identify the "smell-print" of the street.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="map-card reveal">
      <img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="Conversational geometries map — polygon layer">
      <p class="map-caption"><strong>Conversational Geometries (The Polygons)</strong> — Area-based mapping that defines the physical boundaries of social interaction, showing where sound clusters and where silence exists.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="sensory-text-block">
    <div class="sensory-col reveal">
      <p class="col-title">Design Intent</p>
      <p class="col-body">To translate these intangible, overlapping data sets into a rigorous visual framework that captures the fluid, lived experience of the site.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="sensory-col reveal">
      <p class="col-title">System Logic</p>
      <p class="col-body">Each layer operates independently yet becomes meaningful through superposition — the same way memory layers over physical space, blurring the boundary between then and now.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ══ INTENT / GALLERY ══ -->
<section class="proj-section" id="intent">
  <p class="section-label reveal">Output</p>
  <h2 class="section-heading reveal">Intent</h2>

  <div class="gallery-pair">
    <div class="reveal">
      <img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="Gallery wall installation view — warm colourway">
    </div>
    <div class="reveal">
      <img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="Gallery wall installation view — cool colourway">
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="intent-text reveal">This project explores the impact of a World War II bombing in Hackney, London, examining how the event has shaped the physical environment and how it is experienced today. Historical context is translated through motion, sound, and typography.</p>
</section>

<!-- ══ MOTION PIECE ══ -->
<section class="proj-section" id="motion">
  <p class="section-label reveal">Film</p>
  <h2 class="section-heading reveal">Motion Piece</h2>

  <div class="motion-layout">
    <div class="motion-left reveal">
      <img class="motion-macbook" src="data:image/png;base64," alt="Motion piece on MacBook — tunnel animation">
      <a href="https://youtu.be/TTImiA_tfL4" class="motion-link" target="_blank">Watch on YouTube →</a>
    </div>
    <div class="motion-right">
      <p class="motion-desc reveal">The motion piece uses fragmented visuals, restrained colour shifts and ambient sound to construct a disoriented, memory-driven narrative. The visual system draws directly from the sensory cartography data — hexagonal conversation geometries dissolve and re-form as the camera descends through compressed time.</p>
      <div class="stills-grid">
        <div class="reveal">
          <img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="Motion still — orange and pink polygon overlay">
        </div>
        <div class="reveal">
          <img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="Motion still — scattered hexagons dissolving into darkness">
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ══ ZINE ══ -->
<section class="proj-section" id="zine">
  <p class="section-label reveal">Publication</p>
  <h2 class="section-heading reveal">The Zine</h2>

  <div class="zine-wrap reveal">
    <img class="zine-img" src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Bombsite zine — scattered open spreads overhead view">
  </div>
  <p class="zine-caption reveal">The zine is developed from documented interviews and on-site observations, translating personal accounts and overheard conversations into a narrative reflecting collective memory.</p>
</section>

